                    PROCEDURES
    1. Create a folder in the themes directory with your custom theme name.
    2. Create index.php, style.css, screenshot.png (1200*900)
    3. Create header.php, footer.php, functions.php, front-page.php
    4. Admin panel → settings → general →  change site title
    5. Admin panel → settings → reading →  your homepage displays  a static page
    6. Create 404.php page
    7. Create folders for css, js, fonts, images
    8. While creating post you must create single.php and single-post.php
    9. While creating page you must create page.php and different page templates
    10. Page.php for default to all pages
    11. Single.php default to all post pages
    12. Index.php file for blog post default page (when u change in admin panel for posts page)